<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,1536,2029]" pageId="24" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1825,1849]" pageId="24" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[321,518,1824,1848]" class="Malacostraca" family="Isaeidae" genus="Chevalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomasi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[321,518,1824,1848]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="49">Chevalia thomasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[525,614,1825,1849]" pageId="24" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[525,614,1825,1849]" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[759,909,1824,1848]" class="Malacostraca" family="Chevaliidae" genus="Neophotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[759,909,1824,1848]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="49">C. inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both included in the group II, by the pereopod 
<number box="[151,165,1861,1884]" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" value="7.0">7</number>
basis rectangular lacking produced posterodistal corner. But the new species is characterized by the diagnostic features of the accessory flagellum 
<number box="[574,586,1896,1920]" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
–articulate; carpus of gnathopod 
<number box="[977,991,1896,1920]" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
as long as propodus; and the only 
<number box="[1422,1436,1896,1920]" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
submarginal robust seta on posterodistal corner of pereopods 
<number box="[839,885,1932,1956]" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
.
</paragraph>
